Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.http

Enum HTTPVersion

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<HTTPVersion>
      • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.http.HTTPVersion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<HTTPVersion>
    public enum HTTPVersion
extends java.lang.Enum<HTTPVersion>
    Enum of possible HTTP versions.

    This enum handles both traditional HTTP version strings (e.g., "HTTP/1.1") and ALPN negotiation identifiers (e.g., "h2", "h2c") used during protocol negotiation.

    Author:
    Chris Burdess

      • fromString

        public static HTTPVersion fromString​(java.lang.String s)
        Parses an HTTP version from either a version string or ALPN identifier.

        This method first tries to parse as an ALPN identifier, then falls back to parsing as a version string. This handles cases where the input could be either format.

        Parameters:
        s - the string to parse (version string or ALPN identifier)
        Returns:
        the corresponding HTTPVersion, or UNKNOWN if not recognized

      • supportsMultiplexing

        public boolean supportsMultiplexing()

      • requiresHostHeader

        public boolean requiresHostHeader()
